Biography

2024 – Sophomore Season

Saw action in 14 games and earned 11 starts … Finished the season with 102 saves … Posted a goals against average of 15.7 and a save percentage of .392 … Also added 26 ground balls and three caused turnovers … Totaled a career-high 15 saves with a .536 save percentage at Hofstra … Recorded 12 saves in 48:59 minutes of action versus No. 14 Penn … Tallied 11 saves at Monmouth … Tallied 10 saves with a .500 save percentage in 45:00 minutes at VCU … Also registered 10 saves in the win against ECU … Earned CAA Commissioner’s Academic Honor Roll distinction …

2023 – Freshman Season

Saw action in six games … Finished the season with 26 saves and a .419 save percentage … Helped lead W&M to a victory against George Washington, as she played the entire second half and posted a shutout during the final 30 minutes with six saves … Recorded seven saves and two ground balls at Maryland … Earned CAA Commissioner’s Academic Honor Roll distinction …

McDonogh School

Two-year letterwinner as a goalie for head coach Taylor Cummings at McDonogh School … Posted a .505 save percentage as a senior … Earned a spot on the 2021 Highlighter all-star team for district east … Won the team’s Nancy Sebeck Love character award, which is bestowed upon a teammate who shows great character and compassion for all her teammates … Also a three-year letterwinner in squash and won the team’s Eagle award as a senior … Garnered the squad’s Coaches award three times … Leader of the Salsa Club and the Ocean Awareness Club … Earned McDonogh’s Cornucopia award … Member of the honor roll and dean’s list …

Personal Information

Daughter of Sean and Bonnie Wilhelm … Enjoys playing squash, reading, traveling, volunteering, looking out for the environment and spending time with family and friends.
